'''''Myrosma''''' is a genus of plants. Only one species is currently recognized: '''''Myrosma cannifolia''''', the '''cannaleaf myrosma''',<ref>{{PLANTS|id=MYCA3|taxon=Myrosma cannifolia|accessdate=15 July 2015}}</ref> native to northern [[South America]] ([[Brazil]], [[Peru]], [[Bolivia]], [[Suriname]], [[French Guiana]], [[Guyana]]) as well as [[Trinidad]] and the [[Windward Islands]]. It is considered naturalized in [[Haiti]], [[Puerto Rico]] and the [[Leeward Islands]].<ref name="jocelynhall">[http://apps.kew.org/wcsp/namedetail.do?name_id=255061 Kew World Checklist of Selected Plant Families, ''Myrosma'']</ref><ref>[https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/411041#page/23/mode/1up Carl von Linnaeus f. 1782.  Supplementum Plantarum 8, 80.]</ref>

